article.headline: Northeastern 60, William &amp, Mary 44
article.story: BOSTON -- Matt Janning scored 22 points, including five 3-pointers, to lead Northeastern past William & Mary on Saturday, 60-44. Manny Adako added 13 points and Chaisson Allen finished with 12 points and eight rebounds for Northeastern. William & Mary's Danny Sumner scored nine of his team-high 14 points from the free throw line. Quinn McDowell added 12 points and four rebounds. Northeastern (7-5, 2-0 Colonial Athletic Association) shot 52 percent from the floor in the second half as it built on a 30-22 halftime lead. William & Mary (5-7, 0-2) pulled to within 34-30 on a McDowell layup early in the second half, but the Tribe never got closer than four points the rest of the way. William & Mary started the game with a 7-2 run, but Northeastern scored 16 straight -- the final 12 from Janning -- and led 18-7 with 12 minutes left in the first half.
